{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/homepage-status-monitor","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Home is an application I developed last year (Nov-Dec) while learning the MEAN (MongoDB, Express, Angular and NodeJS) stack. It's a homepage status monitor, more or less a glorified bookmark/favourites tool with the ability to scan if ports are open or closed on a host.</p>\n<!-- more -->\n<h3 id=\"problem\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#problem\" aria-label=\"problem permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Problem</h3>\n<p>Every application is made to solve a particular problem. There needs to be a reason to make it.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>There were so many web services and infrastructure at work that not everyone on the team knew which was where and how to access its correct URL.</li>\n<li>There was a need to create transparency.</li>\n<li>Infrastructure monitoring tools weren't up to the task\n<ul>\n<li>Nagios and its clones: overhead using its agents</li>\n<li>StatusPage.io: paid service</li>\n<li>vCenter Operations Manager: only works for virtual machines</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"idea\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#idea\" aria-label=\"idea permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Idea</h2>\n<p>So with the problem in mind, I started prototyping the idea in my head:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>All these services were in my bookmark bar so it work similar to it</li>\n<li>It would be difficult to get complete system monitoring e.g. CPU, memory, disk usage. A simple is it up or down was good enough.</li>\n<li>It has to be configurable and easy to make changes to. This would mean I had to use specific languages and tools to make it work.</li>\n<li>It had to be good enough for everyone, including myself to use on a daily basis.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"plan\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#plan\" aria-label=\"plan permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Plan</h2>\n<p>The plan to build it was based off the ideas I had:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimal and simple approach. This meant a single page design without any page refreshes for any CRUD operations.</li>\n<li>Achieving the single page design meant I needed asynchronous background operations (e.g. AJAX).</li>\n<li>To get asynchronous operations I had to use JavaScript. This was a good chance to finally learn the MEAN stack. The MEAN stack provides the ability to create dynamic web sites using free and open-source solutions.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"execution\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#execution\" aria-label=\"execution permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Execution</h2>\n<p>I programmed it over the period of a month using IntelliJ's WebStorm application. There were no reviews of any kind and I presented it as-is to my team. The results were very positive.</p>\n<h2 id=\"additional-features\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#additional-features\" aria-label=\"additional features permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Additional Features</h2>\n<p>One cheesy feature I threw in was the weather feature. Weather provided by Forecast.io and animated icons from Skycons nicely present the forecast over one week period.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/14116e2980cfee6f454baf7b920a41d6/41314/weather.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.558685446009385%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"weather\"\n        title=\"weather\"\n        src=\"/static/14116e2980cfee6f454baf7b920a41d6/d6170/weather.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/14116e2980cfee6f454baf7b920a41d6/53f68/weather.png 213w,\n/static/14116e2980cfee6f454baf7b920a41d6/df70d/weather.png 425w,\n/static/14116e2980cfee6f454baf7b920a41d6/d6170/weather.png 850w,\n/static/14116e2980cfee6f454baf7b920a41d6/41314/weather.png 1074w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"downloadsource\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#downloadsource\" aria-label=\"downloadsource permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Download/Source</h2>\n<p>You can download it over at GitHub:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/home\">https://github.com/calvinbui/home</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"future\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#future\" aria-label=\"future permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Future</h2>\n<p>If anyone continues my work there were a few things I really wanted to achieve:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Drag and Drop functionality to reorder items and sections</li>\n<li>Pin notices e.g. power outage @ 5pm</li>\n<li>Better user experience with animations and better validation</li>\n<li>Create more than just bookmarks e.g. notes</li>\n<li>More system monitoring</li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"Home is an application I developed last year (Nov-Dec) while learning the MEAN (MongoDB, Express, Angular and NodeJS) stack. It's a homepage…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/calvin.me/calvin.me/master/posts/2015/2015-02-15-homepage-status-monitor/index.md","frontmatter":{"title":"My Homepage Status Monitoring Application","categories":["Programming"],"tags":["home","javascript","mean","monitoring","status"],"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fixed","backgroundColor":"#080808","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/d09f740028b1e253d1d1f6aba77b0ffb/ccc8a/thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/d09f740028b1e253d1d1f6aba77b0ffb/ccc8a/thumbnail.png 150w,\n/static/d09f740028b1e253d1d1f6aba77b0ffb/67d4a/thumbnail.png 300w","sizes":"150px"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/d09f740028b1e253d1d1f6aba77b0ffb/3554d/thumbnail.webp 150w,\n/static/d09f740028b1e253d1d1f6aba77b0ffb/c437f/thumbnail.webp 300w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"150px"}]},"width":150,"height":150}}}}}},"pageContext":{"filter":"/^.*\\/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-homepage-status-monitor\\/.*$/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}